April 21 (Reuters) -    U.S. stock index futures pointed to a flat open on Monday as investors found few reasons to keep buying following a strong rally last week and ahead of a heavy week of corporate earnings. Dow Jones industrial average futures <DJc1> were up 0.06 percent at 16,352, S&P 500 futures <SPc1> were up 0.09 percent at 1,859.6 and Nasdaq 100 futures <NDc1> were up 0.23 percent at 3,531.5. [.N]

